title: Imposter Syndrome and Dealing with Insecurities
description: Feeling insecure or dealing with feelings of doubt and inadequacy often feel like they're just part of the job as an adult. Jessi and Stew discuss how they often feel insecure in their work and home life and the struggles they face as they live out both on social media and more. From traveling and doing classes, to raising babies, those moments of doubt and feeling less-than creep in and can really harm if not identified early, and Jessi and Stew share how they turn those moments around, feel value, and identify their strengths and importance as humans!
